  "title": "Rooting option not working with jekyll when url sync does",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nThe bug is simple, the rooting option doesn't work with Jekyll but url sync work well.\r\nMy unworking conf:\r\n```\r\nexport const search = instantsearch({\r\n  searchClient: algoliasearch('******','********'),\r\n  indexName: '*******',\r\n  rooting: true,\r\n  searchParameters: {\r\n    hitsPerPage: 10\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy working conf:\r\n```\r\nexport const search = instantsearch({\r\n  searchClient: algoliasearch('******','********'),\r\n  indexName: '*******',\r\n  rooting: false,\r\n  urlSync: {\r\n    mapping: {\r\n      q: 'query'\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  searchParameters: {\r\n    hitsPerPage: 10\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\nUse the rooting option on a jekyll project\r\n\r\nA live example helps a lot!   We have a simple online template for you to use for your explanations:\r\n  https://test-dinsic.fr/rechercher/?query=test\r\n(this is the dev access, they will be change in 7 days)\r\nuser: dinsic\r\npswd: supersecure\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nI wish rooting will work before url sync is deprecated\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - OS: iOS \r\n - Browser Chrome\r\n - Version 68\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\r\n",
